      p <span class="speaker">Valerie Chen</span>And then flipping the cart, and then... you kind of had to just walk them through how it worked, like, &ldquo;oh, you need to go through the <a href="http://samjbrenner.com/alphabetapedia/doku.php?id=characters#cashiers">cashiers</a>&rsquo; lines, any of them, but not the other way.&rdquo; They would like to go through the one that&rsquo;s, like, not a cashier, it&rsquo;s, like, the welcome guy. Or they would go on the wrong side of the other - the first - one. [I&rsquo;d] be, like, &ldquo;no, back up, back up.&rdquo; And it was really hard for people to steer, so it would be really hard for them to <a class="binge-annotation" href="#simulations">get into the lane</a>.
